comments: Shamet (LAC) makes marginal contact with Goodwin (ATL) during his drive and doesn't affect his SQBR.
Shamet (LAC) and Reddish (ATL) engage and separate off-ball during the inbound.
During the pick, Reddish (ATL) and Harrell (LAC) engage and disengage without affecting the other's ability to maintain position.
Collins (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Williams (LAC).
McGruder (LAC) slides his hand in a continuous motion off Collins' (ATL) body after the screen and doesn't affect his SQBR.
Harkless (LAC) makes marginal contact to Goodwin's (ATL) arm during the drive, but the contact does not disrupt his dribble or ability to gather the ball.
Harkless (LAC) absorbs the contact from Goodwin (ATL) as he jumps from right to left and stays on his intended trajectory during the driving shot attempt.
McGruder (LAC) grabs and holds Collins' (ATL) arm during the rebound and the contact affects his ability to retrieve the ball.
Hunter (ATL) and McGruder (LAC) make incidental foot to foot contact on the way back down the court.
Reddish (ATL) makes contact to Williams' (LAC) body during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (LAC) engages on the pick from Collins (ATL) and places a hand on his opposite side hip that he immediately slides off his body.
Harrell (LAC) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Hunter (ATL).
Hunter (ATL) and Green (LAC) make incidental contact as they both go for the loose ball during the rebound.
Patterson (LAC) makes marginal contact to Collins' (ATL) arm and does not affect his ability to make his intended pass.
Patterson (LAC) briefly places a hand on Reddish's (ATL) opposite side hip, but he immediately removes it and does not affect Reddish's ability to receive the inbound pass.
Goodwin (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Green's (LAC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Replay review of the foul called on Patterson (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
Hunter (ATL) makes incidental contact with Harrell (LAC) as he makes a natural move toward the ball during the rebound.
Harrell (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Green (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Goodwin (ATL).
Goodwin (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Williams (LAC).
